				<div class="postKicker">
					</div>
				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: Women Are Starting More Businesses (But That Might Not Be Good)</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-06-25T16:29:12+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">June 25, 2014 12:29 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">June 25, 2014 12:29 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/06/25/today-in-small-business-women-are-starting-more-businesses-but-that-might-not-be-good/" data-title="Today in Small Business: Women Are Starting More Businesses (But That Might Not Be Good)" data-description="Looking at Israeli tech start-ups and anti-spam legislation in Canada.">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>The Economy</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Gross domestic product <a href="//www.whitehouse.gov/blog/2014/06/25/third-estimate-gdp-first-quarter-2014">fell 2.9 percent at an annual rate in the first quarter</a>, mostly because of a decline in exports and a slowdown in inventory investment.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ New home sales <a href="//247wallst.com/housing/2014/06/24/may-new-home-sales-skyrocket-to-highest-rate-in-six-years/?">skyrocketed</a> in May to their highest rate in six years, and hereâs what&#8217;s <a href="//seekingalpha.com/article/2284503-whats-behind-the-blowout-in-new-home-sales">behind the blowout</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ More than three-quarters of small-business owners <a href="//www.marketwatch.com/story/surepayroll-small-business-scorecardr-profit-revenues-on-the-rise-for-small-businesses-2014-06-23?">expect to be profitable</a> in the second half of 2014, according to SurePayroll.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Equipment leasing and financing <a href="//www.heraldonline.com/2014/06/24/6084905/equipment-leasing-and-finance.html">activity</a> is down month-over-month but remains ahead of last year.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The Federal Reserve can <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/06/25/business/economy/fed-rate-increase-is-not-seen-as-imminent.html">wait until next year to raise interest rates</a>, according to the president of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The Conference Board&#8217;s <a href="//247wallst.com/economy/2014/06/24/consumer-confidence-returns-to-2008-levels/">consumer confidence</a> index has returned to its 2008 levels.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The national average for a gallon of regular gasoline is 13 cents <a href="//time.com/money/2917414/gas-prices-save-high-summer-2014/">higher than a year</a> ago.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Entrepreneurship</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A post in The Harvard Business Review looks at <a href="//blogs.hbr.org/2014/06/more-women-starting-businesses-isnt-necessarily-good-news/">why women are starting more businesses</a> and why that isn&#8217;t necessarily be a good thing.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ This man <a href="//www.smarta.com/blog/2014/6/andy-puddicombe-the-man-who-went-from-buddhist-monk-to-superstar-tech-founder/">went from Buddhist Monk</a> to superstar tech founder. <span id="more-86771"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Start Up<br />
</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here are eight surging <a href="//mashable.com/2014/06/24/booming-industries/#:eyJzIjoidCIsImkiOiJfMXJhbHZlMTNsaW9pcnozemZqeWdoYWcxMW5fIn0">start-up industries</a> to watch.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ These <a href="//www.csnews.com/node/68720">emerging segments</a> will shape the future of wine.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Cash Flow</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The role of finance teams <a href="//www.aicpa.org/Press/PressReleases/2014/Pages/Role-of-Finance-Teams-Expanding-as-Business-Complexity-Increases-CGMA-Survey.aspx">continues to expand</a> beyond traditional accounting and financial reporting, according to a new survey.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ M-Pesa may be a <a href="//readwrite.com/2014/06/24/m-pesa-versus-bitcoin">better model</a> than Bitcoin for mobile money.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Virtual companies are <a href="//www.smallbizlabs.com/2014/06/virtual-companies-becoming-more-common.html">becoming</a> more common.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Employees</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here&#8217;s why the Gap thinks a <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/6/24/5838278/why-gap-feels-optimistic-about-its-10-minimum-wage">higher minimum wage</a> is good for business.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A poll of small-business owners found that only one in five are <a href="//www.marketwatch.com/story/only-1-in-5-small-businesses-are-hiring-student-workers-this-summer-2014-06-24?">planning to hire</a> student workers this summer.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Why <a href="//www.vox.com/2014/6/24/5837738/the-9-economic-factors-driving-lebron-james-back-into-free-agency">LeBron James is underpaid</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Here&#8217;s the business case against <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/06/25/opinion/redskins-is-bad-business.html?ref=opinion">calling your football team the Redskins</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Washington</strong></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The Supreme Court <a href="www.nytimes.com/2014/06/26/business/media/supreme-court-rules-against-aereo-in-broadcasters-challenge.html">rules against Aereo</a> &#8212; and says the police need a warrant to <a href="www.nytimes.com/2014/06/26/us/supreme-court-cellphones-search-privacy.html">search a cell phone</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Online</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Jerry Seinfeld explains how to not <a href="//www.wired.com/2014/06/internet-rules/">be a jerk</a> in the digital age.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Google gets into the <a href="//www.cnn.com/2014/06/24/tech/web/google-domains/">domain name</a> business.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Technology</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/101784851">PC isnât dead</a> yet, according to one tech supplier.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ The Federal Aviation Administration is taking a hard line <a href="//arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2014/06/faa-grounds-amazons-drone-delivery-plans/">against the commercial use of drones</a>.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Ideas</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ An Ohio business owner <a href="//www.thisweeknews.com/content/stories/germanvillage/news/2014/06/23/store-owner-proposes-electronic-warning-system-for-businesses.html">proposes</a> an electronic crime-alert system for local businesses.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the Country</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A federal judge says the <a href="//boingboing.net/2014/06/24/usas-no-fly-list-is-unconsti.html">no-fly list</a> is unconstitutional.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ Dallas <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/dallas/news/2014/06/24/dallas-home-prices-continue-to-reach-new-highs.html">home prices</a> continue to reach new highs.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A dozen Israeli tech start-ups <a href="//www.breitbart.com/Breitbart-California/2014/06/24/Israeli-Startups-Pitch-Santa-Monica-Techies/">pitch investors</a> and fellow entrepreneurs in Santa Monica, Calif.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Around the World</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ When Canada&#8217;s tough new anti-spam legislation <a href="//www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/new-anti-spam-law-concerns-small-business-operators-1.2685576">kicks in</a> on July 1, businesses that send out unwanted emails and social media messages could face fines.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><b>Health Care</b></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">â¢ A half-decade-long contraction in employer health care spending <a href="//www.cnbc.com/id/101782240#_gus">is set to end</a> in 2015, according to PricewaterhouseCoopers.</p>
